The paper deals with the problem of all pairs similarity search, which is a common problem in information retrieval (IR), databases (DB), and machine learning (ML). The paper proposes a new approach for Locality Sensitive Hashing (LSH), which is a popular technique in data structures (DS) and algorithms (AL). The paper also discusses the use of Bayesian methods, which are commonly used in machine learning and statistics (LG). Finally, the paper proposes a new sequential probability ratio test (SPRT) approach, which is a statistical method commonly used in artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning.
